<D>__{who did this?}
<C>__{julie}
<D>__{stu. that was right about the time we met.}
<C>__{alice}
<D>__{when he first came in to the sleep lab?}
<C>__{julie}
<D>__{yeah...before your time.}
<A>__{the canvas depicts a group of surgeons with the faces of wolves. they're standing over a human patient, replacing his internal organs with machine parts. the style is at once cartoony and unsettling.}
<C>__{alice}
<D>__{jesus, honey...he always joked about you curing him, but i never realized what you cured him from.}
<C>__{julie}
<D>__{he hadn't gotten a good night's sleep in years. the nightmares would wake him up, and he'd start right in painting...}
<P>__{(chuckling)}
<D>__{that boy looked like pluperfect hell.}
<A>__{alice's gaze goes from the nightmare paintings to the monkeybone strips tacked up over the drafting table.}
<C>__{alice}
<D>__{how do you get from here to there?}
